The sector with the most apprehensions for 2010 is Tucson. The sector with the most apprehensions for 2017 is Rio Grande Valley. Then we do a two-sample Welch t-test. As a result, the p-value is 0.06346. Fail to reject the null hypothesis of no change, showing no significant change in the maximum.  


Then we do a two-sample Welch t-test again on 3 month periods with the most apprehensions in 2010 and 2017. As a result, the p-value is 0.4042. Fail to reject the null hypothesis of no change, showing no significant change in the maximum 3 consecutive monthly apprehensions. 

